dishevelled and armadillo act in the wingless signalling pathway in drosophila the nusse lab stanford university skip to main content area login username password request new password home search this site main publications contact wnt homepage home publications dishevelled and armadillo act in the wingless signalling pathway in drosophila submitted by admin on thu 10 14 2010 22 44 title dishevelled and armadillo act in the wingless signalling pathway in drosophila publication type journal article year of publication 1994 authors noordermeer j klingensmith j perrimon n nusse r journal nature volume 367 pagination 80 83 date published jan issn 0028 0836 print 0028 0836 linking abstract the wnt genes encode conserved secreted proteins that play a role in normal development and tumorigenesis little is known about the signal transduction pathways of wnt gene products one of the best characterized wnt family members is the drosophila segment polarity gene wingless we have investigated whether segment polarity genes with a wingless like phenotype mediate the wingless signal we used a wingless transgene controlled by a heat shock promoter for genetic epistasis experiments we show that wingless acts through dishevelled and armadillo to affect the expression of the homeobox gene engrailed and cuticle differentiation doi 10.1038 367080a0 tagged xml bibtex google scholar main publications contact all rights reserved site design by roel nusse and xinhong lim powered by drupal an open source content management system
